                    "company": "Vrije Universiteit Amsterdam (VU Amsterdam)",
                    "description": "The creation and reactivity-study of highly strained organophosphorus compounds was the central theme of my doctorate research. These strained heterocycles are fascinating species from a fundamental point of view, but they are also attractive building blocks as they show intriguing reactivity and remarkably facile rearrangements that gives access to a plethora of novel organophosphorus compounds, such as P-ligands and functional polymers. To achieve this aspiration, reactive intermediate chemistry, supported by high-level theoretical calculations, was used to develop new methodologies and versatile approaches toward applicable and processable building blocks creating unprecedented entries in organophosphorus chemistry.",
